
B-pod wiki: https://sites.google.com/site/bpoddocumentation/home

Kepecs Lab folder: https://github.com/KepecsLab
---

these are the installation steps copied from the wiki

installed sudo apt-get install linux-lowlatency

installed psychtoolbox from this link: 

Ubuntu archive (package octave-psychtoolbox-3)
which opens a the ubuntu software manager

run the matlab script DownloadAdditionsForLinux.m which is in the psychotoolbox folder

---
sudo apt-get install git

git clone  https://github.com/fedecarne/Bpod-ZadorLab.git

git pull

in Matlab: add bpod folder to path

(.gitignore data)
---

do: sudo usermod -a -G dialout "username"

from terminal, launch the editor as root: sudo gedit

Paste the following line into the text editor:

-Dgnu.io.rxtx.SerialPorts=/dev/ttyS0:/dev/ttyS1:/dev/USB0:/dev/ttyACM0

Save the file as java.opts to the following location:

    /usr/local/MATLAB/R2011a/bin/glnxa64

Set the sound subsystem to “no attenuation”. From terminal, run: alsamixer

        Ensure that Card: shows Xonar DX

        Select each slider *EXCEPT for the front L&R* and use the mouse scroll wheel to maximize (0dB gain)

        Press “Esc” to save and exit.

        Without this step, audio card sync pulses will not be sent.

Restart matlab as root

Run Bpod from the command prompt.


----
to synchronize data

sudo apt-get install cifs-utils

sudo mkdir /media/windowsshare

//servername/sharename  /media/windowsshare  cifs  username=msusername,password=mspassword,iocharset=utf8,sec=ntlm  0  0

sudo mount -a





